<font color="#FF0000">TALES FROM THE TOP RAIL</font><br>
<tt>Sun Aug 24 23:56:20 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Ed,<br>
     I love my old P-38, but I don't think I can wax as lyrical about it as you can.  However, I'll second the motion that the story should be real.  I may have a Texas passport, but you and the rest can carry off a brag as the best native Texans I've ever heard. I'll just settle in, pour some peach juice over the pound cake, and knock down any excess flying cans of Chet's Spam with a well aimed ham &amp; lima beans.  <br><br>
Cook,<br>
     Still have my pair of Ho Chi Minh sandals; though my method of acquisition was a bit different, bought them from one of the base's Vietnamese barbers.  When I took them into an 8th grade middle school class; you would have thought I had brought in a pair of gold bars.
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


